Boston’s Cuban culinary gem @gustazocubankitchenandbar 🌟 

With locations in Waltham and Cambridge, Gustazo Cuban Café brings the rich flavors and warm hospitality of Cuba to Greater Boston. Founded in 2011 by James Beard nominated Chef Patricia Estorino and her husband Adolfo, Gustazo is known for bold, ingredient-driven cuisine, craft cocktails, and a welcoming atmosphere. 
Plus, it has a whole lot of vegetarian options on the menu which makes it one of my favorite spots in town 😍

Here are the things we tried:

Drinks -
Guava Blossom
Mango Mojito 

Food -
Croquetas de Hongos (Shiitake Mushroom Croquettes)
Cazuela de Coliflor Asada (Roasted Heirloom Cauliflower)
Frituras de Maiz (Corn Fritters)
Pan Tumaca (Grilled bread with Campari tomatoes)
Ensalada de Habas (Fava beans)

Dessert - Tres Leches (This is one of the BEST Tres Leches that I’ve tried so far ✨)

📍 2067 Massachusetts Ave, Cambridge, MA 02140

A brunch experience like no other! 🍾🍹 @wickedcraftbos 

Get ready to elevate your brunch game with Wicked Craft Co.! This Boston hotspot is serving up more than just regular brunch items - & their brunch parties are LEGENDARY. With an unmatched cocktail menu and a brunch menu that’s full of creative twists and delicious flavors, you’ll want to come back for more. From mimosas to craft cocktails, and from avocado toast to decadent waffles, Wicked Craft Co. has got you covered. Don’t miss out on the fun - gather your squad and get ready for the ultimate brunch experience! 🍳🥂👌

Food we tried:
French toast (MUST try)
Avocado toast 
Tacos 
Strawberry pancakes 

Drinks we tried:

Garden Party

AND we ended our experience with Champagne Pop-tarts with some sparklers ✨ which really made it so much more special 🫶
